ster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"April 23 2014, 09:28:58 UTC","parent":19027592,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://twitter.com/Walrus_Astray","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/twitter-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Walrus_Astray","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1288023","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=50852027&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Walrus_Astray","ctime_ts":1398245338,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/123221584/70300208","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?replyto=19029128","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029128#t19029128","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029128#t19029128","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029128#t19029128","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2546281","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://twitter.com/saint_91","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19029128,"talkid":74332,"etime_ts":"1398078055","thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029128#t19029128","upictitle":"saint_91: pic#123221584","article":"I'm pleased to see the show doing well - I enjoy it immensely most of the time, but I wonder how you feel about deviations from the books that ramp up the sexual violence against women?<br /><br />For example, the TV show turned Daenerys and Drogo's sensual, fully consensual sex into a horrid rape scene. This turns Dany into a girl who falls in love with her rapist instead of a girl who falls for one of the few human beings to show her respect.<br /><br />Last night's scene between Jaime and Cersei in the sept was unequivocally rape, instead of the slightly more ambiguous affair in the novel. In the novel, Cersei's initial denial of consent appears to be due to the fact that they're in the sept, rather than resistance to sex. In the books, the manner in which he continues is a bit troubling, but Cersei seems to go along with it. Though it is from Jaime's perspective and not an outside observer, so perhaps Cersei saw it differently? She certainly doesn't seem happy with him after the event, and she had a history of enduring Robert's sexual advances too. Yet on the show, there is no doubt that Jaime is forcing himself on her. <br /><br />Do you approve of the changes the show has made in this regard? ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"April 21 2014, 10:53:31 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"How do you feel about the manner in which the show deals with rape?","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://twitter.com/saint_91","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/twitter-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"saint_91","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2546281","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=70300208&t=I","alias":0}],"etime":"April 21 2014, 11:00:55 UTC","dname":"saint_91","ctime_ts":1398077611,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?replyto=19034760","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19034760#t19034760","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19034760#t19034760","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19034760#t19034760","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19034760,"talkid":74354,"etime_ts":"1398198992","thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19034760#t19034760","above":19029128,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"I've addressed the scene in the sept already in a comment on the \"Author! Author!\" post.<br /><br />As for Dany's wedding night, I like my own version of the scene, the way I portrayed it in the novel. . . but then, I am hardly objective, am I?  Any writer worth his salt is going to prefer his own take.  <br /><br />Nonetheless, I worked in Hollywood long enough to know that changes are going to happen, even in the most faithful adaptation.  When I adapted Roger Zelazny's \"Last Defender of Camelot\" for TWILIGHT ZONE, I had to make all sorts of changes.  Roger was kind enough to say he liked the show... but I am sure he like his short story more.  <br /><br />We all think our own children are the prettiest.  ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"April 22 2014, 20:35:18 UTC","parent":19029128,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: How do you feel about the manner in which the show deals with rape?","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"etime":"April 22 2014, 20:36:32 UTC","dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1398198918,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/116612666/47806325","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?replyto=19029640","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029640#t19029640","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029640#t19029640","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029640#t19029640","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_1124398","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=706276306","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19029640,"talkid":74334,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029640#t19029640","upictitle":"Calle Johansson: pic#116612666","article":"I discovered the joy that is Doctor Who about a year ago. Considering your love for Sci-Fi and Fantasy, what do you think about GB's largest contribution to the Science Fiction-community? <br /><br />I must say I love the universe they have built, even though it is terribly predictable.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"April 21 2014, 15:54:37 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Doctor Who","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=706276306","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Calle Johansson","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_1124398","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=47806325&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Calle Johansson","ctime_ts":1398095677,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?replyto=19029896","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029896#t19029896","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029896#t19029896","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029896#t19029896","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"guessingo","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19029896,"talkid":74335,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19029896#t19029896","upictitle":"guessingo: pic#0","article":"The Guardian through a fit over the Wheel of Time nomination... The nominations were higher because the WoT fan base organized to nominate the series. I can understand how people can be upset about this, but we never did this before. John Scalzi pointed out that since Worldcon is in England Charlie Stross may get the home town vote. I am voting as a non-attending member. This is my first time voting. <br /><br />I started reading WoT when I was 16 and I finished the last book at 38. Its hard to explain how reading a series over that length of time and starting at 16 means to me. I know George and Robert Jordan were friends. <br /><br />On the James SA Corey front, The Expanse is being made into a TV series (Im sure George knows this). I don't think the quality of SyFy shows is very good (though I liked Battlestar Galactica). I hope they do a good job with it. I would be more hopeful if it was picked up by AMC. I hope they don't turn it into something generic. <br /><br />I believe Ty's co-author Daniel Abraham is working on the Ice and Fire graphic novels right? He is one of my favorite authors. <br /><br />One thing I have complained about for a while with the Hugos... there are several nominations where they don't list the works. As a fan, how would I know what books a specific editor, edited? I am guessing it will be in the Hugo packet (never got one before), but I don't get why they don't list their works next to their names? <br /><br />I also can't figure out the difference between 'semi-pro' and fansite. It strikes me as the same thing. Anyone know? <br /><br />To pivot this back to George... I can't see anything being competitive with the Game of Thrones episode nomination. That is the most well known episode to date. ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"April 21 2014, 16:42:07 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Wheel of Time nomination got attacked by The Guardian","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"guessingo","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"guessingo","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://guessingo.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"guessingo","ctime_ts":1398098527,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/123735554/31972280","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?replyto=19033224","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19033224#t19033224","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19033224#t19033224","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19033224#t19033224","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"urbanflowerpot","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://urbanflowerpot.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":19033224,"talkid":74348,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/367496.html?thread=19033